divs: Sighting DetailsHigginsville, NY. As I stepped out from under my porch, I notice directly above me two aircraft. The first aircraft had static lights that were triangle shaped, the second aircraft was absolutely directly behind the first, and had a box-shaped array of lights. I deliberately noted that I could see the background sky between the 2 objects. I then ran into the house to notify family, who came running out to the front of the house, which we then saw only 1 object (or a cluster of lights that only seemingly would look like 1 aircraft). Although I previously saw the distinction of 2 aircraft with the sky between the two, by the time we all ran out we only saw 1 cluster of lights. What they remarked on was that there were an unusual number of solo blinking lights around the yellow'ed clusters of lights. There had to be about 5 blinking white lights following the cluster of yellow lights. The cluster of yellow lights and accompanying white lights continued from E to NE, at a slight inclination. The fact that there were unusually # of single white lights following this small cluster of yellow lights as it head toward the Syracuse, NY airport was indeed a fact to mention.
